# KaggleSlayer credentials — copy to `.env` and fill in. NEVER commit your real .env.
# The test suite (`pytest -m "not slow"`, 375 tests) needs NONE of these.
# These are only required for a real solve against a live competition.

# Google Gemini API key — get one at https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
# Tier 0 (free) has 0 daily quota for gemini-2.5-pro and ~20 requests/day for
# gemini-2.5-flash; Tier 1 (billing enabled) is recommended for real runs.
# A synthetic-comp solve on gemini-2.5-flash costs ~$0.005–0.02.
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# Kaggle API token — create at https://www.kaggle.com/settings ("Create New Token").
# Use the new KGAT_-prefixed token here, OR set the legacy KAGGLE_USERNAME +
# KAGGLE_KEY pair instead. Needed to download competition data and submit.
KAGGLE_API_TOKEN=
# KAGGLE_USERNAME=
# KAGGLE_KEY=
